eing a soldier, or choose to 'play house.' This requires a radical rethinking of religious questions as no longer just questions of belief or disbelief; but as truths to be tried on, compared, and discarded at will.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aVideo gamesxReligious aspects. 4aContemporary Society. 4aDigital and Social Media. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aGame Studies. 4aMedia Studies. 4aReligion and Theology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh  aVideogames, religion, production studies, consumption studies, qualitative sociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishz978311131926108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023z9783111318806oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048555130?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555130zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048555130/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131926-1 EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSLb2023  aZDB-23-GOA